== Restart !

We want to study interactive protocol, an specialy non local game. But we want to take an other point of view, we want to understand why. Because in the traditionnal model, we say that we have some share ressource and a strategy, and they are a verifier that ask question and receive answer. But it is magig, we don't describe how the interaction happens and how we build this ressource. The consequence is that if we push this model to the limit, we can do thing that is impossible in the real world, for exemple decide the HALT problem.

First we will abstract the background of how the interaction happen and we will suppose directly that we have someone, the narrateur that observe some event (or the event are receive in the narrateur's mind) $e$. The narrateur can receive multiple event, then he can order them with him own time perception ${e_t}$.

We will consider event of this kind $e = (a | x)$ where $a in A_1 crossproduct A_2 dots crossproduct A_n$ and $x in X_1 crossproduct X_2 dots crossproduct X_n$ where $X_i$ is the set of question of player $i$ and $A_j$ the set of answer of player $j$. For example $e = (a b | x y)$ where $a,b in {0,1}$ are the answer of Alice and Bob and $x,y in {0,1}$ are the question of Alice and Bob.

The narrateur can controle the event, he only listen. Maybe he can introduce later actors that can controle the question for example, but for now we will stay simple.

Let define a _trace_ $τ = e_1 e_2 dots e_h$ as a world where the alphabet is the set of event. This means that $τ subset Σ^*$ for $Σ = (A_1 , dots, A_n | X_1 , dots , X_n)$ where $n$ is the number of player that is fixed !

In traditionnal model, we have a probability distribution $p(a b | x y)$ that is purely abstract, we can never observe this quantity directly, but in our model we have a trace $τ$ that is just an observation and we have the property that we can interupt the process at any time.

In the case we are in the classical deterministic model, players has deterministic strategy that is a funcion $f_i (x) = a$ that map the question to the answer. We will take a parallel to the classical setting where alice and bob can share a common random variable $λ$. We have :
$
  p(a b | x y) = sum_λ µ(λ) δ_{a = f_A^λ (x)} δ_{b = f_B^λ (y)}
$
where $µ(λ)$ is the probability distribution of the common random variable and $f_A^λ$ and $f_B^λ$ are the deterministic strategy of Alice and Bob that depend on the common random variable.

In this view point we don't see multiple interation, but we can believe that the common random variable act like a seed, and the deterministic player use this seed to generate strategy that can involve during the time. The players don't have static strategy, but him strategy can evolve during the time. We will say that the *strategy change in a continous way*, this means that if we zoom on a small time window, the strategy of the player is almost constant and a strategy can change only for a strategy that is close to it. This is a form of discret continuity.

